{
  "texts": [
    "Once we have the importance scores δ i, as indicated in Figure 2, we generate a new attention matrix by multiplying the original attention matrix by the importance scores.",
    "This process gives more importance to the attention heads with higher importance scores.",
    "E. Meta-learning based objective functionAs explained, the CNN learns to identify important features in the attention maps and extract attention pruning scores and then, we use a meta-learning process to dynamically adjust attention weights across different tasks.",
    "Meta-learning aims to train our attention pruning model to learn quickly and efficiently on new tasks and the meta-controller is trained on a set of synthetic mini datasets, to learn how to generate attention masks that are task-specific.",
    "For each mini dataset, the meta-controller is trained to produce attention masks that maximize the performance of the pruned BERT model on that task."
  ]
}